## Description

Continues, and probably now finishes my work on improving performance of localizable resources (first part in #9508).

- Replaces around 4 boxing `Hashtable` instances with generic `Dictionary<K, V>`.
- Avoids double-lookups on dictionaries in multiple cases (after migration from `Hashtable` and what was already there).
- Use struct-based enumerator for `BamlLocalizationDictionary`.
    -  Since it is a public type, I just defined them internally.
- Avoids multiple casting and boxing dictionary enumerator; removes boxing `ArrayList` as derrefered storage.
- Fields that can be `readonly` are now `readonly`.
- Unifies formatting in `BamlLocalizationDictionary` as there were about 3 different styles for properties.
    - And I couldn't look at it.
- The benchmarks are pretty much micro scale, think you can imagine this in scale when using it in a standard application (not that anyone uses them!).

